      Safe & Secure Payments

      Frequently Asked Questions

      Check out the queries below for more information.

      Sending money online with ACE money transfer is as easy as it gets. All you need to do is:

      1. Create an account using our website or mobile app.
      2. Complete your profile with basic details and required documents.
      3. Choose the destination country, and desired payout option, and enter the receiver’s details.
      4. Pay for the transaction using your Debit/Credit Card or your Bank Account.

      Do you want to see how these steps work? Click the button below:

      View Tutorial

      You can pay for your online transactions using:

      1. Debit Card
      2. Credit Card
      3. Online Bank Transfer via Trsutly (Except UK)
      4. Ecospend Only from the UK for online bank transfer method.
      5. Google Pay
      6. Apple Pay
      7. Bancontact (Belgium only)
      8. iDeal (Netherlands only)

      To place the transaction, you need to log in to your account. Once the dashboard opens, follow these simple steps:

      1. Click on "Send Money".
      2. Choose the Destination Country.
      3. Select the payout option, i.e., Cash Pick-up or Bank Deposit.
      4. Select the payout location.
      5. Enter the amount.
      6. Create or choose the Beneficiary.
      7. Confirm Bank details (For bank deposit only).
      8. Select the payment method.
      9. Confirm the Payment.

      Do you want to see how these steps work? Click the button below:

      View Tutorial

      Proof of Identity for a Transfer

      We may request any of the following documents as proof of identity for a transfer. All documents must be submitted as real-time, colored pictures:

      Accepted Photo IDs:
      • Passport
      • EU ID card
      • EU Resident Card (requirements vary by sending country)
      • Driving License (not applicable for EU countries)

      1. If you are sending money using a Debit card or Credit card, then mostly transactions are completed in minutes.

      2. If sending money using Online Bank Transfer method, then transactions are completed within 1-2 banking days.

      Following factors may also affect delivery times:

      1. Accuracy of Information (both your personal data and beneficiary details)

      2. Difference in time- zones

      3. Operational working hours (unavailability of banks on weekends and local holidays)

      4. Additional information needs to be collected from you to ensure the security and safety of your transaction

      5. Uncontrollable circumstances, such as a rare instance of downtime affecting one of our business partners

      On our website, click on “Tracker” option from the header and enter your transaction code to check the status.

      If you want to get transaction updates, follow the below steps:

      • Login to the ACE APP
      • Go to "More" Option.
      • Navigate to the settings.
      • Look for the "App Notification" and tap on the "Transaction Updates"
      • You can control different types of notifications from here according to your choice.

      If you want to change your mobile number, follow the below steps:

      If you are using Mobile App

      1. Login to the ACE APP.
      2. Go to "More" Option.
      3. Look for the “Phone Number” option and tap on it.
      4. Enter your New Number and click on request.
      5. You will receive a verification code on your registered email.
      6. Enter the verification code and click “Verify Code”.
      7. You will receive a verification code for your new number.
      8. Enter the code to update your new number.

      If you are using Website

      1. Login to your account.
      2. Go to "My Account" and click the "Mobile Number" option.
      3. Click "Change Mobile Number" and click Next.
      4. Verification An OTP code will be sent to your email.
      5. Enter the OTP code and click "Verify Email Code".
      6. Enter your new number and click on "Verify Mobile Number".
      7. You will receive a verification code for your new number.
      8. Enter the code to update your new number.

      If you want to turn off your notifications, follow the below steps:

      • Login to the ACE APP
      • Navigate to the “Settings”
      • Look for the "App Notification" and tap on it

      You can control different types of notifications from here according to your choice.

      To utilize your previous transaction, follow the below steps:

      • Navigate to the Transaction history
      • Tap on a specific transaction that you want to reuse
      • Look for the “Reuse option” and tap on it
      • Enter your Amount
      • Swipe to pay and complete your transaction

      Customer Fund Safeguarding Practices

      • Segregation of Funds: We maintain a clear separation between customer funds and the company's operational or own funds. Customer funds are placed in designated accounts that are separate from our general business accounts until the customer's transaction has been successfully delivered to the intended beneficiary.
      • Designated Accounts: Customer funds are held in designated bank accounts with reputable financial institutions. These banks are chosen based on their stability and their compliance with local and global regulations.
      • Independent Audits: Regular, independent audits and reconciliations are conducted to ensure that customer funds are correctly segregated and that the firm is in compliance with the regulations. These audits provide additional layers of oversight and verification.

      Apple Pay Availability

      You’ll be able to use Apple Pay for future transactions after successfully completing your first transfer. To make your first transfer, please choose one of the following payment methods:

      1. Debit Card
      2. Credit Card
      3. Online Bank Transfer (availability varies by country)
      4. Google Pay
      5. Bancontact (available in Belgium only)
      6. Blik (available in Poland only)
      7. iDeal (available in the Netherlands only)

      Once your first transfer is completed, Apple Pay will be available as a convenient option for all future transactions.
